Package com.github.tommyettinger.gdcrux

Class PointF5

java.lang.Object
com.github.tommyettinger.gdcrux.Vector5
com.github.tommyettinger.gdcrux.PointF5
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.badlogic.gdx.math.Vector<Vector5>, com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Json.Serializable, com.github.tommyettinger.crux.Point5<PointF5>, com.github.tommyettinger.crux.PointN<PointF5>, Externalizable, Serializable
public class PointF5 extends Vector5 implements com.github.tommyettinger.crux.Point5<PointF5>, com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Json.Serializable, Externalizable
The same as Vector5 (from gdcrux, not libGDX), just implementing Point5, Json.Serializable, and Externalizable. This does have some more additions to those interfaces, such as get(int) and setAt(int, float).

    • fract

      public PointF5 fract()
      Description copied from class: Vector5
      Sets each component so it only has a fractional value, by subtracting the floor from each component. This produces a non-negative float for each component, between 0.0 inclusive and 1.0 exclusive, unless a component is outside the safe range for MathUtils.floor(float) (-16384.0 at the lowest). 
       The result of fract() for a component with a value of  1.25 will be 0.25 .
 The result of fract() for a component with a value of -1.25 will be 0.75 .
      Overrides:
      fract in class Vector5
      Returns:
      this, after modifications
